Create a public interface DisplayText with the below method:
  public void displayText(String text);
Annotate the above interface using  appropriate annotation. 
Note, this interface has only one abstract method.

Write a default method :
  public default String getInput()  -  This method should get a message from the user. (Use Scanner to get the input).
       
Write a public class Main with the below static method. 
  public static DisplayText welcomeMessage() -  In this method implement the lambda expression to print the text received as parameter in the displayText method as 
                                                “Welcome <text>”. 

Write a main method.
- Invoke the above static method. 
- Using that reference invoke the default method getInput.
- Store that String in a variable. 
- Invoke the displayText method by passing this String as parameter.
- The output should be as shown in the sample data below.

Sample Input 1 :
Watson

Sample Output 1 :
Welcome Watson
